
                        Section 2 - Notes
                         ADD Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for ADD instruction
    FROM ubuntu
    ADD text.tar /text
    CMD ["/bin/bash"]

2.  Show tar file on host.

    $ tar tvf text.tar
    -rw-r--r--  0 gail   staff      18 Oct  7 17:00 text1
    -rw-r--r--  0 gail   staff      18 Oct  7 17:01 text2
    -rw-r--r--  0 gail   staff      20 Oct  7 17:01 text3

3.  Show file contents.

    $ cat text?
    This is line one.
    This is line two.
    This is line three.

4.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t add . 

5.  Run container and show tar file extraction.

    $ docker run -it add
    root@15181fef7553:/# ls
    bin   dev  home  lib64  mnt  proc  run   srv  text  usr
    boot  etc  lib   media  opt  root  sbin  sys  tmp   var
    root@15181fef7553:/# cd text
    root@15181fef7553:/text# ls
    text1  text2  text3
    root@15181fef7553:/text# cat text?
    This is line one.
    This is line two.
    This is line three.

